spects as the confrontation of Christian Europe with Islam and the changing role of the Mediterranean from "mare nostrum" to a frontier between nations. Scandinavia, eastern Europe and the Atlantic are also analyzed as boundaries in the context of exploration, migratory movements, cultural exchanges, and war. The Boundaries of Europe, edited by Pietro Rossi, is the first installment in the ALLEA book series Discourses on Intellectual Europe, which seeks to explore the question of an intrinsic or quintessential European identity in light of the rising skepticism towards Europe as an integrated cultural and intellectual region.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a FA license: uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/free-access-policy uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Feb 2021) 0aGeopoliticszEuropexHistory. 0aTerritory, NationalzEurope. 4aEuropäische Integration. 4aGrenzpolitik. 4aTransnationalisierung. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / General.2bisacsh1 aMasoero, Alberto, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMarcone, Arnaldo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStråth, Bo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCardini, Franco, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aElliott, John H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHildermeier, Manfred, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKoller, Markus, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSalvadori, Massimo L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRossi, Pietro, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRossi, Pietro, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc